WEBVTT

1
00:01:36.050 --> 00:01:39.140
I bet we're having another 
meeting until midnight.

2
00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:43.350
Wish someone would lose their shit 
and ruin the meeting.

3
00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:46.480
What is a meeting? 
I don't even know anymore.

4
00:01:48.270 --> 00:01:51.490
This endless run of meetings 
is starting to fray everyone's nerves.

5
00:01:53.610 --> 00:01:55.950
Including mine, to be honest.

6
00:01:56.570 --> 00:01:59.950
Thankfully for me, 
I have the ultimate pick-me-up:

7
00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:03.210
if I line up at Super S's register two, 
I get to see Yamada-san's smile!

8
00:02:45.580 --> 00:02:47.540
Not here tonight, huh?

9
00:02:53.050 --> 00:02:54.720
Thank you! Come again!

10
00:02:54.720 --> 00:02:57.300
Wow, perfect timing!

11
00:03:04.350 --> 00:03:05.730
Let me ring you up.

12
00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:10.060
Welcome.

13
00:03:10.060 --> 00:03:12.400
I-If you would, please.

14
00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:15.360
Sure thing. Do you have your point card?

15
00:03:16.610 --> 00:03:17.360
Here.

16
00:03:17.660 --> 00:03:19.370
Thank you.

17
00:03:20.570 --> 00:03:22.330
Here's your card back.

18
00:03:31.630 --> 00:03:32.590
Sir?

19
00:03:32.590 --> 00:03:33.500
Sir?

20
00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:34.170
Yes?

21
00:03:34.670 --> 00:03:36.970
That'll be 883 yen.

22
00:03:36.970 --> 00:03:39.130
Oh, right.

23
00:03:43.060 --> 00:03:49.440
I'm so grateful she still serves me, even 
after I embarrassed myself like that.

24
00:03:50.350 --> 00:03:53.770
I was the only one who took it too 
seriously! I'm such a fool! A moron!

25
00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:58.610
Please allow me to keep shopping with you!

26
00:03:59.110 --> 00:04:01.530
Spend all your money here!

27
00:04:11.790 --> 00:04:15.590
The client's not responding 
to the apology email I sent them.

28
00:04:15.590 --> 00:04:18.800
I'll never see my family again. 
I'm going to die...

29
00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:21.140
sitting next to this old dude.

30
00:04:21.140 --> 00:04:22.970
Oh, shush, you.

31
00:04:22.970 --> 00:04:25.600
Wait, why are you even doing overtime?

32
00:04:26.220 --> 00:04:29.060
Fixing up the newbie's spreadsheet.

33
00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:31.310
Is she taking advantage of you?

34
00:04:31.310 --> 00:04:34.820
A rookie shouldn't be handling 
this work to begin with.

35
00:04:34.820 --> 00:04:36.530
It was the chief, wasn't it?

36
00:04:36.530 --> 00:04:40.150
He's the one who believes in 
throwing them in at the deep end.

37
00:04:40.150 --> 00:04:43.450
I say he can believe in that 
after he cleans up their messes!

38
00:04:45.410 --> 00:04:49.000
Well, we can't complain. 
The rookie's the one who has it hardest.

39
00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:50.210
Just look at this spreadsheet.

40
00:04:50.460 --> 00:04:53.420
There's no doubt she made it 
to the best of her ability.

41
00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.960
Besides, I have my pick-me-up!

42
00:04:56.960 --> 00:04:58.760
Welcome!

43
00:04:58.760 --> 00:05:00.920
This isn't enough to get me down.

44
00:05:00.920 --> 00:05:04.430
Hey, it's Mister Big Fan over here.

45
00:05:07.310 --> 00:05:08.390
Ack!

46
00:05:08.970 --> 00:05:12.980
Gah! I undid all the fixes I made!

47
00:05:14.150 --> 00:05:16.730
We're partying all night!

48
00:05:18.730 --> 00:05:20.990
Thank you very much.

49
00:05:20.990 --> 00:05:22.280
Thank you.

50
00:05:22.990 --> 00:05:24.910
And she wasn't here.

51
00:05:24.910 --> 00:05:29.660
The universe is telling me off for looking 
to another person for a pick-me-up.

52
00:05:30.750 --> 00:05:33.670
Maybe I should pick up some kind of hobby.

53
00:05:33.670 --> 00:05:35.210
Sasaki-san.

54
00:05:36.380 --> 00:05:38.250
'Sup?

55
00:05:40.010 --> 00:05:44.340
I'm the only one in the smoking 
area now. Wanna join me?

56
00:05:49.180 --> 00:05:53.520
Tayama-san! 
I've been wanting to talk to you!

57
00:05:54.140 --> 00:05:58.400
How could you tell Yamada-san 
to her face that I'm a fan of hers?

58
00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:01.530
I've been dying of embarrassment 
every time I've lined up for her since.

59
00:06:01.530 --> 00:06:03.780
Yeah, and you still do it.

60
00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:06.660
Where is she even watching from?

61
00:06:12.870 --> 00:06:15.670
Sorry I did you like that, Sasaki-san.

62
00:06:18.290 --> 00:06:21.210
But it made Yamada-san really happy.

63
00:06:21.210 --> 00:06:23.670
She said as much, remember?

64
00:06:23.670 --> 00:06:28.180
I've lived too long 
to take that at face value, okay?

65
00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:31.680
Yeah? So, is that all you wanted 
to talk to me about?

66
00:06:32.180 --> 00:06:33.680
Oh, and also...

67
00:06:34.230 --> 00:06:36.440
For you, if you'd like.

68
00:06:36.690 --> 00:06:40.940
As thanks for letting me 
smoke here the other night.

69
00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:42.320
Hey, I know these.

70
00:06:42.320 --> 00:06:46.950
You recognize Yummy 
Mochi Chips? I love them.

71
00:06:46.950 --> 00:06:50.950
They're really popular 
with the senior citizens.

72
00:06:51.450 --> 00:06:53.620
So now I'm entering gramps territory.

73
00:06:54.330 --> 00:06:58.750
I've been wanting to try them, 
so thanks, Sasaki-san.

74
00:06:58.750 --> 00:07:01.460
Well, don't just stand around. 
Have a seat and smoke one.

75
00:07:01.750 --> 00:07:05.720
Oh? My elderly taste actually worked out?

76
00:07:05.720 --> 00:07:08.720
Tayama-san's always 
subverting expectations!

77
00:07:09.180 --> 00:07:12.600
I just finished my shift, 
and I'm feeling peckish.

78
00:07:12.600 --> 00:07:14.770
Don't eat more than half.

79
00:07:14.770 --> 00:07:17.390
You don't want to go 
to bed feeling all stuffed.

80
00:07:21.190 --> 00:07:26.320
I left my smokes at work. 
I don't have any on me.

81
00:07:27.450 --> 00:07:29.360
You can have mine, then.

82
00:07:29.780 --> 00:07:31.870
I can't just bum off you.

83
00:07:32.990 --> 00:07:34.040
Here, smoke this one.

84
00:07:36.710 --> 00:07:38.120
Tayama-san...

85
00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:43.090
If you'd rather eat 
the chips instead, just say so.

86
00:07:43.090 --> 00:07:46.470
Hey, you're really perceptive.

87
00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:51.220
Do you enjoy messing 
with this old guy or something?

88
00:07:51.220 --> 00:07:52.640
Very much so.

89
00:07:52.640 --> 00:07:54.260
Yeah, I figured!

90
00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:59.060
I can't help it. You're my pick-me-up.

91
00:07:59.060 --> 00:08:01.360
Wh-What's that supposed to mean?

92
00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:04.690
It's the same deal as why you line up 
at Yamada-san's register.

93
00:08:05.610 --> 00:08:08.070
You're poking fun at me again.

94
00:08:08.070 --> 00:08:12.450
I swear I've never messed with 
Yamada-san like you're doing to me.

95
00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:15.120
Do you not get it?

96
00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:17.960
We all get our little pick-me-ups 
in different ways.

97
00:08:17.960 --> 00:08:19.830
So quit sulking,

98
00:08:20.290 --> 00:08:22.580
and come again, Sasaki-san.

99
00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:28.470
I'll have you know I am not sulking!

100
00:08:33.300 --> 00:08:35.260
Morning.

101
00:08:41.560 --> 00:08:44.020
Did you hash it out with the client?

102
00:08:44.020 --> 00:08:49.440
You betcha. My highly honed 
apology skills came in handy.

103
00:08:52.070 --> 00:08:54.160
Were you the one who brought 
these mochi chips?

104
00:08:54.160 --> 00:08:55.910
How'd you know?

105
00:08:55.910 --> 00:08:59.540
Don't be silly. Do you have any idea 
how many times you've fed me these?

106
00:08:59.540 --> 00:09:00.660
Oh...

107
00:09:00.660 --> 00:09:03.920
Once you start, you can't stop.

108
00:09:03.920 --> 00:09:06.840
They go well with booze, too. 
Go ahead and take the bag home.

109
00:09:06.840 --> 00:09:09.420
Yeah, you bet I will!

110
00:09:10.220 --> 00:09:12.930
But how do you have so many?

111
00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:16.430
Did you actually buy them 
in bulk or something?

112
00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:18.770
I keep buying them 
when I go to the supermarket.

113
00:09:19.180 --> 00:09:22.060
I forgot I had some at home, 
so I ended up with extras.

114
00:09:22.440 --> 00:09:25.230
Wha? Just quit buying them, then.

115
00:09:25.230 --> 00:09:28.530
But then I wouldn't have anything 
to buy at the supermarket.

116
00:09:28.530 --> 00:09:31.320
Then just don't go 
to the damn supermarket!

117
00:09:50.170 --> 00:09:51.470
Welcome.

118
00:09:55.010 --> 00:09:58.180
These chips you always buy 
sure are good, aren't they?

119
00:09:58.180 --> 00:10:01.850
Huh? Do you like them too, Yamada-san?

120
00:10:01.850 --> 00:10:05.730
I do. I only found out recently, though.

121
00:10:05.730 --> 00:10:09.110
I got given some, and I really liked them.

122
00:10:09.110 --> 00:10:10.980
Now I keep snacking on them.

123
00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:13.450
Someone gave her some... recently?

124
00:10:13.450 --> 00:10:15.490
Mochi chips yummy.

125
00:10:15.950 --> 00:10:19.030
Wait, could it be?

126
00:10:19.490 --> 00:10:22.000
Are Yamada-san and Tayama-san...

127
00:10:24.370 --> 00:10:27.210
really good friends?

128
00:10:28.040 --> 00:10:29.170
Let's have these.

129
00:10:29.170 --> 00:10:31.170
Wow, thanks!

130
00:10:32.630 --> 00:10:35.010
Hay fever, Yamada-chan?

131
00:10:35.510 --> 00:10:41.350
Nah. I just get the feeling some dense 
geezer out there's daydreaming about me.
